1A, and find\nthat the temporal evolution behavior of its blackbody component can be well\ninterpreted with a time-varying $(\\eta,\\sigma_0)$ at the central engine,\ninstead of invoking a varying engine base size $r_0$ as proposed by previous\nauthors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Sep 2014 20:05:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 Jan 2015 02:57:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
