{"id":"1409.3752","submitter":"Jingzhi Yan","authors":"Jingzhi Yan (IMJ)","title":"Existence of periodic points near an isolated fixed point with Lefschetz\n  index $1$ and zero rotation for area preserving surface homeomorphisms","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1017/etds.2015.18","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $f$ be an orientation and area preserving diffeomorphism of an oriented\nsurface $M$ with an isolated degenerate fixed point $z_0$ with Lefschetz index\none. Le Roux conjectured that $z_0$ is accumulated by periodic orbits. In this\narticle, we will approach Le Roux's conjecture by proving that if $f$ is\nisotopic to the identity by an isotopy fixing $z_0$ and if the area of $M$ is\nfinite, then $z_0$ is accumulated not only by periodic points, but also by\nperiodic orbits in the measure sense. More precisely, the Dirac measure at\n$z_0$ is the limit in weak-star topology of a sequence of invariant probability\nmeasures supported on periodic orbits. Our proof is purely topological and will\nworks for homeomorphisms and is related to the notion of local rotation set.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Sep 2014 14:37:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-15"}
